Problem:
--------
Given an integer array of size n, find the maximum of the minimums for every window size from 1 to n.For each specific window size k (where 1<=k<=n):
Find all possible contiguous subarrays (windows) of size k.Determine the minimum element within each of these windows.
Find the maximum value among all those minimums.Output this maximum value for every k from 1 to n.

Example:
Input Array: [10, 20, 30, 50, 10, 70, 30]
Output Array: [70, 30, 20, 10, 10, 10, 10]

Explanation:
Window size k=1:
Windows: [10], [20], [30], [50], [10], [70], [30]
Minimums: 10, 20, 30, 50, 10, 70, 30
Maximum of minimums = 70

Window size k=2:
Windows: [10,20], [20,30], [30,50], [50,10], [10,70], [70,30]
Minimums: 10, 20, 30, 10, 10, 30
Maximum of minimums = 30

Similarly, for all window size.

Solution:
--------
class Solution{
    public static int[] maxOfMin(int[] arr, int n) {
        int left[] = new int[n];
        int right[] = new int[n];
        Stack<Integer> stack = new Stack<>();
        
        // 1. Find indices of previous smaller elements:Left[] 
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            while (!stack.isEmpty() && arr[stack.peek()] >= arr[i]) {
                stack.pop();
            }
            left[i] = stack.isEmpty() ? -1 : stack.peek();
            stack.push(i);
        }
        stack.clear();//reuse stack

        // 2. Find indices of next smaller elements:right[]
        for (int i = n - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            while (!stack.isEmpty() && arr[stack.peek()] >= arr[i]) {
                stack.pop();
            }
            right[i] = stack.isEmpty() ? n : stack.peek();
            stack.push(i);
        }

        // 3. Create an answer array initialized to 0
        int ans[] = new int[n + 1]; 

        // 4. Fill answer array based on maximum window length for each element
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            int len = right[i] - left[i] - 1;
            ans[len] = Math.max(ans[len], arr[i]);
        }

        // 5. Some entries might be empty. Fill them from right to left.
        // A maximum for window size 'x' is also valid for window size 'x-1'
        for (int i = n - 1; i >= 1; i--) {
            ans[i] = Math.max(ans[i], ans[i + 1]);
        }

        // Return results ignoring 0th index (sizes 1 to n)
        return Arrays.copyOfRange(ans, 1, n + 1);
      }
    }
    Time Complexity: O(N)
    Space Complexity: O(N)
